article.description: Josh Hagins scored 20 points and grabbed nine rebounds and Arkansas-Little Rock saw most of its 28-point halftime lead disappear, but held on to beat UT-Arlington, 68-62 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Little Rock loses big lead, holds off UT-Arlington, 68-62
article.linkText: Little Rock loses big lead, holds off UT-Arlington, 68-62
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- Josh Hagins scored 20 points and grabbed nine rebounds and Arkansas-Little Rock saw most of its 28-point halftime lead disappear, but held on to beat UT-Arlington, 68-62 on Saturday night. Little Rock used an 18-0 run to start the game and led 42-14 at the break. Then the teams switched roles. Drew Charles hit back-to-back 3-pointers to start the second half and Little Rock did not score for the first three minutes. Erick Neal hit a pair of 3-pointers that cut the Trojans' lead to four points in the final two minutes, but could get no closer. Little Rock (17-2, 7-1 Sun Belt) finished 24 of 51 from the field, including 9 of 25 from beyond the arc. Kennedy Eubanks scored 14 points and Drew Charles and Neal each added 12 for UT-Arlington (14-4, 5-2). The Mavericks shot 20 of 67 from the field and 9 of 38 from behind the arc.
